- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper applies the proposed method to neuroimaging datasets, which often involve image processing and analysis techniques. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper focuses on analyzing neuroimaging time series data, which is closely related to the study of neural networks and brain activity. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper deals with graphical models, which are commonly used to represent social and information networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper discusses the information encoded in the low-rank structure of the model, which is a topic of interest in information theory.
